    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture of the Peoria, an Algonquian-speaking people whose ancestral land was located east of the Mississippi River and north of the Ohio River. They were assigned land in "Indian Territory" after the Omnibus Treaty in 1867; today they are a federally-recognized tribe with headquarters in Miami, Oklahoma. </Note_Text>
